article.description: Carter Hendricksen had 22 points as North Florida defeated Lipscomb 82-74 on Saturday.
article.headline: Hendricksen leads North Florida past Lipscomb 82-74
article.linkText: Hendricksen leads North Florida past Lipscomb 82-74
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. -- Carter Hendricksen had 22 points as North Florida defeated Lipscomb 82-74 on Saturday. JT Escobar had 15 points for North Florida (19-11, 12-3 Atlantic Sun Conference), which earned its sixth straight home victory. Ivan Gandia-Rosa added 13 points and 12 assists. Wajid Aminu had 12 points and nine rebounds. Ahsan Asadullah had 17 points, 14 rebounds and nine assists for the Bisons (13-15, 8-7), whose five-game win streak was broken. Michael Buckland added 15 points, six rebounds and three blocks. Greg Jones had 14 points. The Ospreys evened the season series against the Bisons with the win. Lipscomb defeated North Florida 85-73 on Jan. 25. North Florida finishes out the regular season against Stetson on the road on Thursday. Lipscomb finishes out the regular season against Liberty at home next Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
